Label: HTANParentBiospecimenID
Description: HTAN Biospecimen Identifier (eg HTANx_yyy_zzz) indicating the biospecimen(s) from which these files were derived; multiple parent biospecimen should be comma-separated

Label: AssayType
Description: The type and level of assay this metadata applies to (e.g. RPPA, Nanostring DSP, etc.)

Label: HTANDataFileID
Description: Self-identifier for this data file - HTAN ID of this file HTAN ID SOP (eg HTANx_yyy_zzz)

Label: Component
Description: Category of metadata (e.g. Diagnosis, Biospecimen, scRNA-seq Level 1, etc.); provide the same one for all items/rows.

Label: filename
Description: Name of a file

Label: fileFormat
Description: Format of a file (e.g. txt, csv, fastq, bam, etc.)
Valid Values: ['m', 'pdf', 'Sentrix descriptor file', 'czi', 'cell am', 'avi', 'mzML', 'sra', 'json', 'html', 'gzip', 'svg', 'gtf', 'DICOM', 'idat', 'am', 'bedgraph', 'cloupe', 'hdf5', 'gff3', 'wiggle', 'mtx', 'dat', 'bpm', 'fasta', 'flagstat', 'abf', 'plink', 'svs', 'md', 'bigwig', 'dup', 'fastq', 'chp', 'doc', 'sqlite', 'tar', 'sav', 'sam', 'bed gappedPeak', 'sdf', 'tif', 'powerpoint', 'cel', 'png', 'rmd', 'gct', 'fig', '7z', 'locs', 'mpg', 'pzfx', 'mov', 'bed', 'xml', 'msf', 'bai', 'maf', 'excel', 'tsv', 'bed narrowPeak', 'jpg', 'sif', 'raw', 'zip', 'ab1', 'mex', 'bam', 'RData', 'csv', 'tagAlign', 'Python script', 'hyperlink', 'bcf', 'tiff', 'recal', 'OME-TIFF', 'bed broadPeak', 'vcf', 'tranches', 'idx', 'seg', 'R script', 'bgzip', 'hic', 'txt']

Label: ProcessingDaysfromIndex
Description: Number of days from the research participant's index date that the biospecimen was processed

Label: HistologyAssessmentMedium
Description: The method of assessment used to characterize histology

Label: FixativeType
Description: Text term to identify the type of fixative used to preserve a tissue specimen
Valid Values: ['None', 'Polaxamer', 'NP40 lysis buffer', 'Formalin', 'Carbodiimide', 'Dimidoester', 'TCL lysis buffer', 'Glutaraldehyde', '95% Ethanol', 'PAXgene tissue', "Carnoy's Fixative", 'Saline', 'Alcohol', 'Other', 'Cryo-store', 'OCT media', 'unknown', 'Methacarn', 'RNAlater', 'Dimethylacetamide', 'Para-benzoquinone', 'Acetone']

Label: PercentNormalCells
Description: Numeric value to represent the percentage of normal cell content in a malignant tumor sample or specimen.

Label: StorageMethod
Description: The method by which a biomaterial was stored after preservation or before another protocol was used.
Valid Values: ['Frozen in liquid nitrogen', 'Not Applicable', 'RNAlater at 25C', 'unknown', 'Frozen at -150C', 'Refrigerated at 4 degrees', 'Frozen at -70C', 'Cut slide', 'Fresh', 'Desiccant at 4C', 'Frozen in vapor phase', 'Paraffin block', 'Frozen at -80C', '4C in vacuum chamber', 'Refrigerated vacuum chamber', 'RNAlater at -20C', 'Ambient temperature', 'RNAlater at 4C']

Label: ProtocolLink
Description: Protocols.io ID or DOI link to a free/open protocol resource describing in detail the assay protocol (e.g. surface markers used in Smart-seq, dissociation duration,  lot/batch numbers for key reagents such as primers, sequencing reagent kits, etc.) or the protocol by which the sample was obtained or generated.

Label: HistologyAssessmentBy
Description: Text term describing who (in what role) made the histological assessments of the sample

Label: NumberProliferatingCells
Description: Numeric value that represents the count of proliferating cells determined during pathologic review of the sample slide(s).

Label: Component
Description: Category of metadata (e.g. Diagnosis, Biospecimen, scRNA-seq Level 1, etc.); provide the same one for all items/rows.

Label: CollectionMedia
Description: Material Specimen is collected into post procedure

Label: PercentLymphocyteInfiltration
Description: Numeric value to represent the percentage of infiltration by lymphocytes in a solid tissue normal sample or specimen.

Label: PercentGranulocyteInfiltration
Description: Numeric value to represent the percentage of infiltration by granulocytes in a tumor sample or specimen.

Label: PercentNeutrophilInfiltration
Description: Numeric value to represent the percentage of infiltration by neutrophils in a tumor sample or specimen.

Label: SlicingMethod
Description: Imaging specific: the method by which the tissue was sliced.

Label: MethodofNucleicAcidIsolation
Description: Bulk RNA & DNA-seq specific: method used for nucleic acid isolation. E.g. Qiagen Allprep, Qiagen miRNAeasy. [Text - max length 100]

Label: TimepointLabel
Description: Label to identify the time point at which the clinical data or biospecimen was obtained (e.g. Baseline, End of Treatment, Overall survival, Final). NO PHI/PII INFORMATION IS ALLOWED.

Label: PercentNecrosis
Description: Numeric value to represent the percentage of cell death in a malignant tumor sample or specimen.

Label: AdjacentBiospecimenIDs
Description: List of HTAN Identifiers (separated by commas) of adjacent biospecimens cut from the same sample; for example HTA3_3000_3, HTA3_3000_4, ...

Label: FiducialMarker
Description: Imaging specific: fiducial markers for the alignment of images taken across multiple rounds of imaging.
Valid Values: ['Not Reported', 'unknown', 'Fluorescent Beads', 'Nuclear Stain - DAPI', 'Adhesive Markers', 'Grid Slides - Hemocytometer', 'Other', '']

Label: MountingMedium
Description: The solution in which the specimen is embedded, generally under a cover glass. It may be liquid, gum or resinous, soluble in water, alcohol or other solvents and be sealed from the external atmosphere by non-soluble ringing media
Valid Values: ['PBS', 'Aqueous water based', 'Non-Aqueous Solvent based', 'Not Reported', 'Antifade without DAPI', 'unknown', 'Toluene', 'Antifade with DAPI', 'Xylene', '']

Label: PercentStromalCells
Description: Numeric value to represent the percentage of reactive cells that are present in a malignant tumor sample or specimen but are not malignant such as fibroblasts, vascular structures, etc.

Label: PercentMonocyteInfiltration
Description: Numeric value to represent the percentage of monocyte infiltration in a sample or specimen.

Label: CollectionDaysfromIndex
Description: Number of days from the research participant's index date that the biospecimen was obtained.

Label: SiteDataSource
Description: Text to identify the data source for the specimen/sample from within the HTAN center, if applicable. Any identifier used within the center to identify data sources. No PHI/PII is allowed.

Label: PercentInflamInfiltration
Description: Numeric value to represent local response to cellular injury, marked by capillary dilatation, edema and leukocyte infiltration; clinically, inflammation is manifest by redness, heat, pain, swelling and loss of function, with the need to heal damaged tissue.

Label: DegreeofDysplasia
Description: Information related to the presence of cells that look abnormal under a microscope but are not cancer. Records the degree of dysplasia for the cyst or lesion under consideration.
Valid Values: ['Carcinoma in Situ', 'unknown', 'Normal or basal cell hyperplasia or metaplasia', 'Mild dysplasia', 'Severe dysplasia', 'Moderate dysplasia', '']

Label: AcquisitionMethodType
Description: Records the method of acquisition or source for the specimen under consideration.
Valid Values: ['Re-excision', 'Shave Biopsy', 'Fine Needle Aspirate', 'Not specified', 'Punch Biopsy', 'BAL (bronchial alveolar lavage)', 'Endoscopic biopsy', 'Sentinel Node Biopsy', 'Lymphadenectomy - Regional Nodes', 'Induced sputum', 'Surgical Resection', 'Forceps biopsy', 'Other Acquisition Method', 'Excision', 'Cytobrush', 'Autopsy', 'Fluid collection', 'Blood draw', 'Non induced sputum', 'Core needle biopsy', 'Biopsy']

Label: PercentEosinophilInfiltration
Description: Numeric value to represent the percentage of infiltration by eosinophils in a tumor sample or specimen.

Label: PercentTumorNuclei
Description: Numeric value to represent the percentage of tumor nuclei in a malignant neoplasm sample or specimen.

Label: HTANParentID
Description: HTAN ID of parent from which the biospecimen was obtained. Parent could be another biospecimen or a research participant.

Label: DysplasiaFraction
Description: Resulting value to represent the number of pieces of dysplasia divided by the total number of pieces. [Text: max length 5]

Label: PercentTumorCells
Description: Numeric value that represents the percentage of infiltration by tumor cells in a sample.

Label: PreinvasiveMorphology
Description: Histologic Morphology not included in ICD-O-3 morphology codes, for preinvasive lesions included in the HTAN
Valid Values: ['Melanoma in situ - acral-lentiginous', 'Atypical adenomatous hyperplasia', 'Squamous metaplasia - mature', 'Atypical melanocytic proliferation', 'Normal WDA', 'Carcinoma NOS', 'Moderate dysplasia', 'Benign tumor NOS', 'Squamous metaplasia - immature', 'Invasive melanoma - desmoplastic', 'Squamous Carcinoma in situ', 'Reserve cell hyperplasia', 'Mild dysplasia', 'Melanoma in situ - lentigo maligna type', 'No diagnosis possible', 'Invasive melanoma - acral lentiginous', 'Adenocarcinoma in situ - mucinous', 'Persistent melanoma in situ', 'Invasive melanoma - nevoid', 'Hamartoma', 'Invasive melanoma - nodular type', 'Invasive melanoma - superficial spreading', 'Adenocarcinoma in situ - non mucinous', 'Invasive melanoma - lentigo maligna', 'Scar - no residual melanoma', 'Melanoma in situ - superficial spreading', 'Melanocytic hyperplasia', 'Invasive melanoma - other', 'Melanoma in situ - arising in a giant congenital nevus', 'Severe dysplasia', 'Melanoma in situ - not otherwise classified', '']

Label: HTANBiospecimenID
Description: HTAN ID associated with a biosample based on HTAN ID SOP (eg HTANx_yyy_zzz)

Label: ProcessingLocation
Description: Site with an HTAN center where specimen processing occurs, if applicable. Any identifier used within the center to identify processing location. No PHI/PII is allowed.

Label: TumorInfiltratingLymphocytes
Description: Measure of Tumor-Infiltrating Lymphocytes [Number]

Label: BiospecimenType
Description: Biospecimen Type
Valid Values: ['Tissue Biospecimen Type', 'Analyte Biospecimen Type', 'Ascites Biospecimen Type', 'Stool Biospecimen Type', 'Mouth Rinse Biospecimen Type', 'Sputum Biospecimen Type', 'Cells Biospecimen Type', 'Urine Biospecimen Type', 'Bone Marrow Biospecimen Type', 'Fluids Biospecimen Type', 'Blood Biospecimen Type']

Label: LysisBuffer
Description: scRNA-seq specific: Type of lysis buffer used

Label: AcquisitionMethodOtherSpecify
Description: A custom acquisition method [Text - max length 100 characters]
Conditional Requirements: Acquisition Method Type -is- "Other Acquisition Method"

Label: BiospecimenDimension2
Description: Second dimension of tissue fragment (number, up to one decimal place) measured in units as defined by the "dimensions_unit" CDE
Conditional Requirements: Biospecimen Type -is- "Tissue Biospecimen Type" || Biospecimen Type -is- "Bone Marrow Biospecimen Type"

Label: TotalVolume
Description: Numeric value for the total amount of sample or specimen
Conditional Requirements: Biospecimen Type -is- "Tissue Biospecimen Type" || Biospecimen Type -is- "Urine Biospecimen Type" || Biospecimen Type -is- "Bone Marrow Biospecimen Type"

Label: BiospecimenDimension1
Description: First dimension of tissue fragment (number, up to one decimal place) measured in units as defined by the "dimensions_unit" CDE
Conditional Requirements: Biospecimen Type -is- "Tissue Biospecimen Type" || Biospecimen Type -is- "Bone Marrow Biospecimen Type"

Label: BiospecimenDimension3
Description: Third dimension of tissue fragment (number, up to one decimal place) measured in units as defined by the "dimensions_unit" CDE
Conditional Requirements: Biospecimen Type -is- "Tissue Biospecimen Type" || Biospecimen Type -is- "Bone Marrow Biospecimen Type"

Label: SpecimenLaterality
Description: For tumors in paired organs, designates the side on which the specimen was obtained.
Conditional Requirements: Biospecimen Type -is- "Tissue Biospecimen Type" || Biospecimen Type -is- "Urine Biospecimen Type" || Biospecimen Type -is- "Bone Marrow Biospecimen Type"

Label: SectionNumberinSequence
Description: Numeric value (integer, including ranges) provided to a sample in a series of sections (list all adjacent sections in the Adjacent Biospecimen IDs field)
Conditional Requirements: Biospecimen Type -is- "Tissue Biospecimen Type" || Biospecimen Type -is- "Bone Marrow Biospecimen Type"

Label: HistologicMorphologyCode
Description: Histologic Morphology Code, based on ICD-O-3. Any valid ICD-O-3 morphology code. See https://seer.cancer.gov/icd-o-3/ and https://seer.cancer.gov/icd-o-3/sitetype.icdo3.20200629.xlsx. Examples: 80510
Conditional Requirements: Biospecimen Type -is- "Tissue Biospecimen Type" || Biospecimen Type -is- "Urine Biospecimen Type" || Biospecimen Type -is- "Bone Marrow Biospecimen Type"

Label: IschemicTime
Description: Duration of time, in seconds, between when the specimen stopped receiving oxygen and when it was preserved or processed. Integer value.
Conditional Requirements: Biospecimen Type -is- "Tissue Biospecimen Type" || Biospecimen Type -is- "Analyte Biospecimen Type" || Biospecimen Type -is- "Urine Biospecimen Type" || Biospecimen Type -is- "Bone Marrow Biospecimen Type"

Label: PortionWeight
Description: Numeric value that represents the sample portion weight, measured in milligrams.
Conditional Requirements: Biospecimen Type -is- "Tissue Biospecimen Type" || Biospecimen Type -is- "Urine Biospecimen Type" || Biospecimen Type -is- "Bone Marrow Biospecimen Type"

Label: PreservationMethod
Description: Text term that represents the method used to preserve the sample.
Valid Values: ['Fresh dissociated', 'Fresh dissociated and single cell sorted', 'Cryopreservation in dry ice - dead tissue', 'Formalin fixed-unbuffered', 'Snap Frozen', 'Fresh', 'Cryopreservation in liquid nitrogen - live cells', 'Cryopreserved', 'Liquid Nitrogen', 'Not Reported', 'Fresh dissociated and single cell sorted into plates in NP40 buffer', 'Methacarn fixed paraffin embedded - MFPE', 'Fresh dissociated and single cell sorted into plates', 'unknown', 'Formalin fixed-buffered', 'OCT', 'Formalin fixed paraffin embedded - FFPE', 'Frozen', 'Negative 80 Deg C', 'Cryopreservation in liquid nitrogen - dead tissue', '']
Conditional Requirements: Biospecimen Type -is- "Tissue Biospecimen Type" || Biospecimen Type -is- "Urine Biospecimen Type" || Biospecimen Type -is- "Bone Marrow Biospecimen Type"

Label: IschemicTemperature
Description: Specify whether specimen experienced warm or cold ischemia.
Valid Values: ['4C wet ice', 'Warm Ischemia', 'Liquid Nitrogen', 'Cold Ischemia', 'Negative -20C', 'unknown', 'Dry Ice', 'Ambient air', '']
Conditional Requirements: Biospecimen Type -is- "Tissue Biospecimen Type" || Biospecimen Type -is- "Analyte Biospecimen Type" || Biospecimen Type -is- "Urine Biospecimen Type" || Biospecimen Type -is- "Bone Marrow Biospecimen Type"

Label: TumorTissueType
Description: Text that describes the kind of disease present in the tumor specimen as related to a specific timepoint (add rows to select multiple values along with timepoints)
Valid Values: ['Metastatic', 'Post therapy', 'Post therapy neoadjuvant', 'Primary', 'Normal adjacent', 'Premalignant - in situ', 'Atypia - hyperplasia', 'Premalignant', 'Local recurrence', 'Recurrent', 'Normal distant', 'Normal', 'Not Otherwise Specified', 'Additional Primary', 'Post therapy adjuvant', '']
Conditional Requirements: Biospecimen Type -is- "Tissue Biospecimen Type" || Biospecimen Type -is- "Urine Biospecimen Type" || Biospecimen Type -is- "Bone Marrow Biospecimen Type"

Label: SlideChargeType
Description: A description of the charge on the glass slide.
Conditional Requirements: Biospecimen Type -is- "Analyte Biospecimen Type"

Label: SectionThicknessValue
Description: Numeric value to describe the thickness of a slice to tissue taken from a biospecimen, measured in microns (um).
Conditional Requirements: Biospecimen Type -is- "Analyte Biospecimen Type"

Label: AnalyteType
Description: The kind of molecular specimen analyte: a molecular derivative (I.e. RNA / DNA / Protein Lysate) obtained from a specimen
Valid Values: ['PBMCs or Plasma or Serum Analyte', 'DNA Analyte', 'cfDNA Analyte', 'RNA Analyte', 'PBMCs', 'Total RNA Analyte', 'Tissue Section Analyte', 'Serum Analyte', 'cDNA Libraries Analyte', 'Plasma', 'Tissue Block Analyte', '']
Conditional Requirements: Biospecimen Type -is- "Analyte Biospecimen Type"

Label: FixationDuration
Description: The length of time, from beginning to end, required to process or preserve biospecimens in fixative (measured in minutes)
Conditional Requirements: Biospecimen Type -is- "Analyte Biospecimen Type"

Label: SectioningDaysfromIndex
Description: Number of days from the research participant's index date that the biospecimen was sectioned after collection
Conditional Requirements: Biospecimen Type -is- "Analyte Biospecimen Type"

Label: ShippingConditionType
Description: Text descriptor of the shipping environment of a biospecimen.
Valid Values: ['Dry Ice', 'Liquid Nitrogen', 'Not Shipped', 'Ice Pack', 'Other Shipping Environment', 'Specimen at Room Temperature', 'Ambient Pack', 'Cold Pack', '']
Conditional Requirements: Biospecimen Type -is- "Analyte Biospecimen Type" || Biospecimen Type -is- "Blood Biospecimen Type"

Label: TotalVolumeUnit
Description: Unit of measurement used for the total amount of sample or specimen

Label: DimensionsUnit
Description: Unit of measurement used for dimension CDEs in metric system (i.e. cm, mm, etc)

Label: HTANParticipantID
Description: HTAN ID associated with a patient based on HTAN ID SOP (eg HTANx_yyy )

Label: DaystoBirth
Description: Number of days between the date used for index and the date from a person's date of birth represented as a calculated negative number of days.

Label: MedicallyUnderservedArea
Description: Areas or populations designated by HRSA as having too few primary care providers, high infant mortality, high poverty or a high elderly population:  Use patient zip code to find the county the patient lives in by going to https://www.unitedstateszipcodes.org/ - enter the zip code in the main text field and use the associated county on the right side of the result field. Go to data.hrsa.gov website and select "Query Data". Pick the Medically Underserved Areas/Populations (MUA/P) data source in the step 1 menu and select "View Data". Enter the name of the county (_______ county) in the first "Service Area" column, adding the state in the 5th column may help direct you to the data.  If the designation type in the third column is "medically underserved area" enter "Yes" as the value. If the county generates a "No data available in table" enter "No" as the value.  A value of "Unknown" indicates that sufficient data was not available to look up the value.  If value is yes, complete the Medically_underserved_score data element.
Valid Values: ['Medically Underserved Area - Yes', 'Medically Underserved Area - Unknown', 'Medically Underserved Area - No', '']

Description: Indicator that describes if cancer treatment was modified for the patient due to COVID-19 infectious disorder

Description: Text term that retrospectively indicates the worst complications during COVID-19 infectious disorder in the patient.

Label: CancerIncidence
Description: Incidence of specific cancer type in a defined area (a number between 0 and 100). The rate of incident cases per population of 100,000 persons of a specific type of cancer as designated in the "primary_diagnosis" data element in the county where the patient resides, using the most recent 2013-2017 NCI Cancer Atlas derived data.  Use patient zip code to find the county the patient lives in by going to https://www.unitedstateszipcodes.org/. Enter the zip code in the main text field and use the asociated county on the right side of the result field. On the https://gis.cancer.gov/canceratlas/tableview/ website, choose "Incidence" from the Topic dropdown menu, state of interest from the Area menu, "All Races" from the Race menu, and the cancer type ("Both Sexes" when possible) from the Statistic menu. Find the county of interest and enter the numeric Age-Adjusted Rate per 100,000 as the value.

Label: MedicallyUnderservedScore
Description: Index of Medical Underservice (IMU) score, a number between 0 and 100, where 0 represents completely underserved and 100 represents best served or least underserved. Use patient zip code to find the county the patient lives in by going to https://www.unitedstateszipcodes.org/. Enter the zip code in the main text field and use the asociated county on the right side of the result field. Go to data.hrsa.gov website and select Query Data. Pick the Medically Underserved Areas/Populations (MUA/P) data source in the step 1 menu and select View Data. Enter the name of the county (______ county) in the first "Service Area" column, adding the state in the 5th column may help direct you to the data. Enter the Index of Medical Underservice Score in the fourth column to one decimal place as the value.
Conditional Requirements: Medically Underserved Area -is- "Medically Underserved Area - Yes"

Label: InternationalPrognosticIndex
Description: The text term used to describe the International Prognostic Index, which classifies the prognosis of patients with aggressive non-Hodgkin's lymphoma.

Label: AnaplasiaPresentType
Description: The text term used to describe the morphologic findings indicating the presence of a malignant cellular infiltrate characterized by the presence of large pleomorphic cells, necrosis, and high mitotic activity in a tissue sample.

Label: NonNodalTumorDeposits
Description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe the presence of tumor deposits in the pericolic or perirectal fat or in adjacent mesentery away from the leading edge of the tumor.

Label: SynchronousMalignancy
Description: A yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether the patient had an additional malignant diagnosis at the same time the tumor used for sequencing was diagnosed. If both tumors were sequenced, both tumors would have synchronous malignancies.

Label: FirstSymptomPriortoDiagnosis
Description: Text term used to describe the patient's first symptom experienced prior to diagnosis and thought to be related to the disease.
Valid Values: ['Seizures', 'Not Reported', 'Sensory Changes', 'unknown', 'Visual Changes', 'Headaches', 'Motor or Movement Changes', 'Altered Mental Status', '']

Label: VascularInvasionPresent
Description: The yes/no indicator to ask if large vessel or venous invasion was detected by surgery or presence in a tumor specimen.
Valid Values: ['Not Reported', 'unknown', 'Not Allowed To Collect', 'No', 'Yes - Vascular Invasion Present', '']

Label: MarginsInvolvedSite
Description: The text term used to describe the anatomic sites that were involved in the survival margins.

Label: MitosisKaryorrhexisIndex
Description: Text term that represents the component of the International Neuroblastoma Pathology Classification (INPC) for mitosis-karyorrhexis index (MKI).

Label: Component
Description: Category of metadata (e.g. Diagnosis, Biospecimen, scRNA-seq Level 1, etc.); provide the same one for all items/rows.

Label: AnaplasiaPresent
Description:
Yes/no/unknown/Not Reported indicator used to describe whether anaplasia was present at the
time of diagnosis.

Label: IRSGroup
Description: Text term used to describe the classification of rhabdomyosarcoma tumors, as defined by the Intergroup Rhabdomyosarcoma Study (IRS).
Valid Values: ['Not Reported', 'Group I', 'unknown', 'Group IV', 'Group IIc', 'Group IIIb', 'Group III', 'Group IIa', 'Group Ib', 'Group II', 'Group Ia', 'Group IIIa', '']

Label: TumorDepth
Description: Numeric value that represents the depth of tumor invasion, measured in millimeters (mm).

Label: GleasonGradeGroup
Description: The text term used to describe the overall grouping of grades defined by the Gleason grading classification, which is used to determine the aggressiveness of prostate cancer. Note that this grade describes the entire prostatectomy specimen and is not specific to the sample used for sequencing.

Label: MetastasisatDiagnosis
Description: The text term used to describe the extent of metastatic disease present at diagnosis.

Label: AJCCPathologicN
Description:
The codes that represent the stage of cancer based on the nodes present (N stage) according
 to criteria based on multiple editions of the AJCC's Cancer Staging Manual.

Label: WHOCNSGrade
Description: WHO CNS Grade
Valid Values: ['Not Reported', 'Grade III', 'unknown', 'Grade Not Assigned', 'Grade II', 'Grade I', 'Grade IV', '']

Label: AJCCPathologicStage
Description:
The extent of a cancer, especially whether the disease has spread from the original site to
 other parts of the body based on AJCC staging criteria.
Valid Values: ['Stage IIB', 'Not Reported', 'Stage IB2', 'Stage IB1', 'Stage II', 'Stage IIA1', 'Stage IA2', 'Stage IA', 'Stage I', 'Stage IVB', 'Stage IIC', 'Stage IC', 'Stage 0a', 'unknown', 'Stage IA1', 'Stage IIIB', 'Stage X', 'Stage III', 'Stage IIA', 'Stage 0', 'Stage IVA', 'Stage Tis', 'Stage IIC1', 'Stage IIIC', 'Stage 0is', 'Stage IVC', 'Stage IIIC1', 'Stage IB', 'Stage IIA2', 'Stage IIIC2', 'Stage IIIA', 'Stage IS', 'Stage IV', '']

Label: IGCCCGStage
Description: The text term used to describe the International Germ Cell Cancer Collaborative Group (IGCCCG), a grouping used to further classify metastatic testicular tumors.

Label: ResidualDisease
Description: Text terms to describe the status of a tissue margin following surgical resection.

Label: Morphology
Description: The third edition of the International Classification of Diseases for Oncology, published in 2000 used principally in tumor and cancer registries for coding the site (topography) and the histology (morphology) of neoplasms. The study of the structure of the cells and their arrangement to constitute tissues and, finally, the association among these to form organs. In pathology, the microscopic process of identifying normal and abnormal morphologic characteristics in tissues, by employing various cytochemical and immunocytochemical stains. A system of numbered categories for representation of data.

Label: PrimaryGleasonGrade
Description: The text term used to describe the primary Gleason score, which describes the pattern of cells making up the largest area of the tumor. The primary and secondary Gleason pattern grades are combined to determine the patient's Gleason grade group, which is used to determine the aggresiveness of prostate cancer. Note that this grade describes the entire prostatectomy specimen and is not specific to the sample used for sequencing.

Label: Laterality
Description: For tumors in paired organs, designates the side on which the cancer originates.

Label: NonNodalRegionalDisease
Description: The text term used to describe whether the patient had non-nodal regional disease.

Label: PriorTreatment
Description: A yes/no/unknown/not applicable indicator related to the administration of therapeutic agents received before the body specimen was collected.

Label: GrossTumorWeight
Description: Numeric value used to describe the gross pathologic tumor weight, measured in grams.

Label: AJCCPathologicT
Description:
Code of pathological T (primary tumor) to define the size or contiguous extension of the
 primary tumor (T), using staging criteria from the American Joint Committee on Cancer
 (AJCC).

Label: PerineuralInvasionPresent
Description: A yes/no indicator to ask if perineural invasion or infiltration of tumor or cancer is present.

Label: StartDaysfromIndex
Description: Number of days from the date of birth (index date) to the date of an event (e.g. exposure to environmental factor, treatment start, etc.). If not applicable please enter 'Not Applicable'

Label: PancreaticIPMNPathologyEpithelialSubtype
Description: The Intraductal Papillary Mucinous Neoplasm (IPMN) epithelial cell subtype based on the gross and microscopic examination of a pancreatic neoplasm specimen

Label: Component
Description: Category of metadata (e.g. Diagnosis, Biospecimen, scRNA-seq Level 1, etc.); provide the same one for all items/rows.

Label: PancreasPrecancerHistopathologicGrade
Description: The grade of precancerous pancreatic tissue based on microscopic study of characteristic tissue abnormalities by employing various cytochemical and immunocytochemical stains.

Label: StopDaysfromIndex
Description: Number of days from the date of birth (index date) to the end date of the event (e.g. exposure to environmental factor, treatment start, etc.). Note: if the event occurs at a single time point, e.g. a diagnosis or a lab test, the values for this column is 'Not Applicable'

Label: TimepointLabel
Description: Label to identify the time point at which the clinical data or biospecimen was obtained (e.g. Baseline, End of Treatment, Overall survival, Final). NO PHI/PII INFORMATION IS ALLOWED.

Label: PancreaticDuctFinalPathologyType
Description: The final pathology result of the pancreatic duct communication type.

Label: HTANParticipantID
Description: HTAN ID associated with a patient based on HTAN ID SOP (eg HTANx_yyy )

Label: TreatmentIntentType

Label: NumberofCycles

Label: TreatmentFrequency

Description: Percentage value to represent result of Forced Expiratory Volume in 1 second (FEV1) divided by the Forced Vital Capacity (FVC) pre-bronchodilator.

Description: Text term used to describe the patient's menopause status.

Label: CD4Count
Description: The text term used to describe the outcome of the procedure to determine the amount of the CD4 expressing cells in a sample.

Label: HAARTTreatmentIndicator
Description: The text term used to indicate whether the patient received Highly Active Antiretroviral Therapy (HAART).

Label: ImmunosuppressiveTreatmentType
Description: The text term used to describe the type of immunosuppresive treatment the patient received.

Description: Number of days between the date used for index and the date the patient was diagnosed with a comorbidity.

Label: HysterectomyType
Description: The text term used to describe the type of hysterectomy the patient had.

Label: FEV1RefPostBronchPercent
Description: The percentage comparison to a normal value reference range of the volume of air that a patient can forcibly exhale from the lungs in one second post-bronchodilator.

Description: Text term used to describe the classification used of the functional capabilities of a person.

Description: The yes/no indicator that records if the subject has undergone a previous colonoscopy.

Label: StartDaysfromIndex
Description: Number of days from the date of birth (index date) to the date of an event (e.g. exposure to environmental factor, treatment start, etc.). If not applicable please enter 'Not Applicable'

Label: ColorectalCancerDetectionMethodType
Description: The means, manner of procedure, or systematic course of actions performed in order to discover or identify colorectal cancer
Valid Values: ['Colonoscopy', 'DNA stool test', 'Fecal occult blood test', 'unknown', 'Virtual colonoscopy', 'Data not available', 'Other', 'Sigmoidoscopy', '']

Label: ColorectalPolypAdenomaType
Description: Type of adenoma associated with the polyp
Valid Values: ['Villous', 'Tubular', 'Not stated', 'Tubulovillous', 'Not Applicable', 'Traditional serrated', 'Sessile serrated', 'Serrated not specified', '']

Label: HTANParticipantID
Description: HTAN ID associated with a patient based on HTAN ID SOP (eg HTANx_yyy )

Label: FamilyColonCancerHistoryIndicator
Description: The indicator to designate if any first degree relative has a history of colorectal cancer.

Label: ColorectalPolypType
Description: Type of polyp found in the participant

Label: ImmediateFamilyHistoryOvarianCancer
Description: Text that describes the age at which the family member was diagnosed with ovarian cancer in relationship to their 50th birthday.

Label: MLH1PromoterMethylationStatus
Description: Text term to define the status of promoter methylation for the MLH1 gene. Note: MLH1 gene is commonly associated with hereditary nonpolyposis colorectal cancer. Testing for methylation of the MLH1 promoter can help distinguish sporadic from inherited cancers.

Label: Component
Description: Category of metadata (e.g. Diagnosis, Biospecimen, scRNA-seq Level 1, etc.); provide the same one for all items/rows.

Label: ColorectalCancerTumorBorderConfiguration
Description: The description of the border configuration of a colorectal tumor at pathologic assessment.

Label: SizeofPolypRemoved
Description: Size of the polyp removed in cm

Label: FamilyHistoryColorectalPolyp
Description: A yes/no/unknown/not applicable indicator related to family medical history diagnosis of polypoid lesion that arises from the colon or rectum and protrudes into the lumen.

Label: HistoryofPriorColonPolyps
Description: Yes/No indicator to describe if the subject had a previous history of colon polyps as noted in the history/physical or previous endoscopic report (s).

Label: ColonPolypOccurenceIndicator
Description: Yes/No indicator to describe if the subject had a previous history of colon polyps as noted in the history/physical or previous endoscopic report (s).

column1: Patient Inflammatory Bowel Disease Personal Medica History
Attribute: Patient Inflammatory Bowel Disease Personal Medica History
Label: PatientInflammatoryBowelDiseasePersonalMedicaHistory
Description: The indicator for patient's personal medical history of inflammatory bowel disease (chronic, non-specific disorders of unknown etiology, including Crohn disease and ulcerative colitis).

Label: ColorectalPolypNewIndicator
Description: A yes/no response to a question that asks whether any new polyps greater or equal to two millimeter were identified.
